Bank Account

Define a class to represent a bank account. Include the following members: Data members: 1) Name of the depositor 2) Account number 3) Type of account 4) Balance amount in the account. Member functions: 1) To assign initial values 2) To deposit an amount 3) To withdraw an amount after checking the balance 4) To display name and balance. Write a java program to print the details of bank account.

Input and Output Format

Refer sample Input and Output

Sample Input

Enter Details:                                                                                                                                  

Accout No: 1234                                                                                                                                 

Name: Raj                                                                                                                                                                                                                      

Account Type: Saving                                                                                                                                                                          

Balance: 50000                

Enter Deposit Amount = 14000                                                                                                                                                                                          

Enter Withdraw Amount = 49000

Sample Output                                                                                                                          

Accout No: 1234                                                             

Name: Raj                                                                                                                                       

Account Type: Saving                                                                                                                            

Balance: 15000
import java.util.*;
class Bank1
{
    public void display()
    {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter Details:");
        System.out.print("Accout No: ");
        int a=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Name: ");
        String b=sc.next();
        System.out.print("Account Type: ");
        String c=sc.next();
        System.out.print("Balance: ");
        int d=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter Deposit Amount = ");
        int e=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.print("Enter Withdraw Amount = ");
        int f=sc.nextInt();
        int g=(d+e)-f;
        System.out.println("Accout No: "+a);
        System.out.println("Name: "+b);
        System.out.println("Account Type: "+c);
        System.out.println("Balance: "+g);
        
        
    }
}
 class Bank extends Bank1
 {
     public static void main(String[] args)
     {
         Bank1 b=new Bank1();
         b.display();
     }
 }

